componentInstanceProperties.value: The NDIS/Aged Care Property Opportunity [Webinar Recap]

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The world of property investment is ever-evolving, with opportunities emerging in niche markets. One such niche is Specialist Disability Accommodation (SDA) and Aged Care accommodation and both are areas of pressing need within the community. 

VentureCrowd recently hosted a webinar, "The NDIS/Aged Care Property Opportunity," where our property experts, David Whitting (VentureCrowd’s Head of Property) and Brad Beh (VentureCrowd’s Senior Development Manager) shared valuable insights on this high-demand sector. In this webinar recap, we'll dive into the top highlights from the webinar.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: Growing demand for Specialist Disability Accommodation (SDA)

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
David shed light on the significant and rising demand for Specialist Disability Accommodation (SDA). He mentioned, "There's a specialist disability accommodation market insights report by a group called Summer Foundation, and it found that the existing supply of SDA needs to grow by 60 percent to house 28,000 people that the NDIS expects to fund."

He emphasised the changing landscape of the NDIS, stating, "NDIS spending is going to be increasing by about 700 million dollars a year when the scheme is fully implemented with the SDA accounting for the majority of it. The shift from the previous grants-based funding to a market-based system where individuals have control over their own funding will create a 5 billion disability housing market over the next 5 years."

Watch the segment here [04:28].

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The Moggill Ferry Road project presented a unique opportunity, as described by David: "We were presented this opportunity by another group. We will take the benefit of the option over the land, which sits there for 18 months effectively, we'll look to get the approval, and we'll talk a little bit about the information that we've got in relation to that approval to date, and then we will look to on-sell the opportunity."

Brad Beh added to this, "We discovered an operator who instantly flagged an interest in the project. And we started pulling together a consultant team from there."

Watch the segment here [10:50].

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Brad Beh introduced the essential role of Victorious Community Foundation, saying, "In stumbling across Victorious, they've been flying under the radar, and we've been digging deep into their operation. They have several core businesses that actually back the Victorious Foundation as a not-for-profit."

He continued, "They're prepared to sign a lease to take up the entirety of the project, obviously underpinned by federal government-funded rental schemes."

Watch the segment here [13:00].

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: The plan going forward for Moggill Ferry Road

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Brad provided insights into the future of the Moggill Ferry Road project: "The scheme, as it stands at this point in time, is actually code accessible. However, obviously, there are a lot of technical aspects that we have to run through, namely flood hydraulics."

David outlined the development's stageable and easily buildable nature. He stated, "So there are potentially three of the six towers first up, and then as the demand grows, those are other towers that can be delivered."

Watch the segment here [15:11].

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Jason, VentureCrowd’s Capital Manager and co-host of the webinar highlighted the investment opportunity: "Via ordinary equity, we're offering up to 60 percent return on equity, which is an IRR annualised return forecasted at 40%."

David summed it up with an example based on forecasted returns. He said, "We anticipate returning 60% return on equity. That means if you invest $100,000, you get $160,000 back [forecasted return] over 18 months."

Watch the segment here [21:04].

VentureCrowd is committed to bringing more projects like this to our investors, not only in NDIS but other high-impact projects. To discuss this deal and future impactful property deals, book a call with one of our friendly team members today.
